content_vision: A person thinks they've found the love of their life, and gives it their all, only to be badly let down.
text:
Intro:
My heart was open, but you took it for granted
thought you were the one, but now I've been disenchanted.

Verse 1:
Thought we had a connection, but it was all just one-sided,
now I see the truth, it was all just lies and pretense divided.
Thought I had finally found my forever,
but you only saw me as a temporary endeavor.
Thought I was your queen, but you treated me like a pawn,
constantly hurt and used, but now I'm finally moving on.
I was blinded by your charms,
but now I see the cracks,

Pre-Chorus 1:
Thought we were building a future,
but you were just busy tearing me down

Chorus 1:
I was your all, but to me,
you were nothing but a fall.
But now I see the truth,
you were nothing but a con,

Verse 2:
But now I see the real you, hiding behind the facade,
You were never capable of giving me the love I truly desired and I see that now, so flawed.
But now I see the real you, hiding behind the facade, You were never capable of giving me the love I truly desired and I see that now,
so flawed.
But I won't let your betrayal break me,
I'll rise above and find my own destiny.
But your lies and deceit, they were my breaking point,
thoughts of you still haunt me, but I'll heal and anoint.

Chorus 2:
I was addicted to the fantasy you sold me, but
now I see the reality and it's nothing but empty.
But now I see the reality, and it's a shame,
You never loved me, it was just a twisted game.

Bridge:
But I won't let your betrayal break me,
I'll rise above and find my own destiny
But now I see you for who you truly are, a player in a game of love,
but I won't let you leave me scarred.

Outro:
But I won't let your betrayal define me, I'll
rise above and find my own destiny and leave you behind

Solo:
But now I see the truth, you were just a player in a game of love, manipulating my heart like a puppet on a string,
my love for you was just a fling but I'm moving on and spreading my wings.

Instrumental:
my heartstrings were your instrument,
but you played me like a fool.
